      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(twiml): preserve base path prefix when building WebSocket and TwiML URLs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- `new URL(\"/twilio\", base)` is an absolute-path reference per the URL spec — it **replaces** the entire path of the base URL. So `VOX_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://host/vox` would produce `wss://host/twilio` instead of `wss://host/vox/twilio`, silently breaking any path-prefixed reverse-proxy setup.\n- Fix `wsUrlFromPublicBase` in `src/twiml.ts` to concatenate onto the base pathname directly.\n- Fix the same bug in `src/cli.ts` where `vox dial` builds its TwiML URL fallback.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nPure URL string transformation — fully deterministic, exercised without a network connection.\n\nBefore the fix:\n```\nwsUrlFromPublicBase(new URL(\"https://example.com/vox\"), \"/twilio\")\n→ \"wss://example.com/twilio\"  // prefix dropped\n```\n\nAfter the fix:\n```\nwsUrlFromPublicBase(new URL(\"https://example.com/vox\"), \"/twilio\")\n→ \"wss://example.com/vox/twilio\"  // preserved\n```\n\n```\n# Subtest: wsUrlFromPublicBase preserves a base path prefix\nok 1 - wsUrlFromPublicBase preserves a base path prefix\n```\n\nTrailing-slash normalization also covered (`https://example.com/vox/` → `wss://example.com/vox/twilio`, no double slash).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm run lint`\n- [x] `pnpm run typecheck`\n- [x] `pnpm test` — 57/57 passing, including:\n  - `test/twiml.test.ts` — existing protocol-conversion test still passes; new path-prefix test catches the regression\n- [x] `pnpm run build`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
